![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1608740364242-O0YL1IX7L7JA63TO3XQJ/Burning157.jpg?format=original)

It took Diana Prince aka Wonder Woman over 75 years to make her cinematic debut with the relatively unknown Gal Gadot in the title role. After a stellar debut in Batman V Superman, many wondered how a Wonder Woman film would fair. Let's take a trip back to 2017 revisit the cultural touchstone that is the first Wonder Woman film as we talk Ares, Chris Pine and Gal Gadot's chemistry, and the depiction of the Amazons en route to Wonder Woman 1984.**  
  
Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
